  "texts": [
    "This must be performed in real-time, with latency below 100 ms, to elicit an unperceivable delay for users 140.",
    "This architecture will constitute a neuromorphic sensory neuroprosthesis.",
    "At the core of the closed-loop biomimetic prosthesis lies the ability to seamlessly capture, process, and transmit tactile/pressure information.",
    "Neuromorphic hardware can process in real-time such information and, by mimicking the intricate neural encoding mechanisms of the somatosensory system, can enable artificial limbs to provide users with natural and informative feedback (Fig. 3).",
    "Then, the intact nervous system does the rest: the signals from the residual nerves are conveyed to the brain of the user, who is able to perceive what happens at the prosthesis and adjust the motor behavior accordingly."
  ]
}